<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 29, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Audited and corrected pages that overclaimed species support ("all species" / "every species") or listed an incomplete subset of the nine species BreederHQ actually supports. BreederHQ supports nine species: dogs, cats, horses, goats, alpacas, llamas, rabbits, sheep, and cattle — and the site now says so consistently.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Overclaim fixes ("every species" / "all species" used as a hero/category-wide promise)</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Animal Facilities hub (<a href="/facilities" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/facilities</a>):</strong> H1 changed from "Bookable Spaces for Every Species" to "Bookable Spaces for the Species We Support."</li>
    <li><strong>Boarding Facilities provider page (<a href="/for-providers/boarding-facilities" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/boarding-facilities</a>):</strong> "trusted boarding for every species" replaced with an explicit nine-species enumeration.</li>
    <li><strong>Boarding hub (<a href="/facilities/boarding" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/facilities/boarding</a>):</strong> CTA tagline "Every species, one platform" changed to "Nine species, one platform."</li>
    <li><strong>Why BreederHQ Marketplace (<a href="/buyers/why-breederhq-marketplace" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/buyers/why-breederhq-marketplace</a>):</strong> FAQ answer about marketplace species coverage now lists all nine species and bounds the service-provider claim to "the species BreederHQ supports."</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Incomplete species-list fixes (lists that omitted alpacas, llamas, and/or cattle)</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Home (<a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/</a>):</strong> Meta description now includes cattle.</li>
    <li><strong>FAQ / pricing / find-breeders / for-breeders surfaces:</strong> All nine species listed everywhere the platform's supported species are enumerated.</li>
    <li><strong>Using the Marketplace (<a href="/buyers/using-the-marketplace" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/buyers/using-the-marketplace</a>):</strong> Species search filter list now includes alpacas, llamas, and cattle.</li>
    <li><strong>Best Breeding Software hub (<a href="/compare/best-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/best-breeding-software</a>):</strong> "and more" replaced with the explicit nine-species list in both the FAQ and body copy.</li>
    <li><strong>Health Tests buyer guide (<a href="/buyers/health-tests" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/buyers/health-tests</a>):</strong> Meta description now lists all nine species.</li>
    <li><strong>Find Breeders index (<a href="/find-breeders" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/find-breeders</a>):</strong> Meta description now includes cattle.</li>
    <li><strong>Nutrition Tracking (<a href="/workflows/nutrition-tracking" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/nutrition-tracking</a>):</strong> Species-support callout for nutrition products now lists all nine species.</li>
    <li><strong>Breeding Management Software article (<a href="/articles/breeding-management-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/articles/breeding-management-software</a>):</strong> "alpacas, llamas, and similar species" replaced with the explicit nine-species list.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Left intentionally unchanged</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-1">
    <li>Article copy that uses "Not all platforms support all species" or "treat all species the same" as criticism of competing software — those phrases are not BreederHQ claims.</li>
    <li>Protocol Builder, Buyer Application Builder, and Scout AI references to "any species" — those tools are genuinely user-built / parsing-based and are species-agnostic in scope.</li>
    <li>Comparison hub meta description ("across all species") — describes the comparison topic, not BreederHQ's coverage.</li>
    <li>Per-page subtitles already qualified as "every species the marketplace serves" or "every species the platform serves."</li>
  </ul>
